<item>
            <title>[LU-11612] Potential null pointer dereference in new_init_ucred</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11612</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The code looks like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
        setgid = ((pud-&amp;gt;pud_gid != pud-&amp;gt;pud_fsgid) ||
                  (ucred-&amp;gt;uc_identity &amp;amp;&amp;amp;
                   (pud-&amp;gt;pud_gid != ucred-&amp;gt;uc_identity-&amp;gt;mi_gid)));
...
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (setgid &amp;amp;&amp;amp; !(perm &amp;amp; CFS_SETGID_PERM)) {
                CDEBUG(D_SEC, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;mdt blocked setgid attempt (%u:%u/%u:%u -&amp;gt; %u) &quot;&lt;/span&gt;
                       &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;from %s\n&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, pud-&amp;gt;pud_uid, pud-&amp;gt;pud_gid,
                       pud-&amp;gt;pud_fsuid, pud-&amp;gt;pud_fsgid,
                       ucred-&amp;gt;uc_identity-&amp;gt;mi_gid, libcfs_nid2str(peernid));
                GOTO(out, rc = -EACCES);
        }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So the posssibility seems to be pretty real though typically D_SEC is not defined so no crash like that by default.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
